 Grant of citizenship 



 5. (1) The Minister grants citizenship to any person who: 



 (a) requests it; 



 (b) is at least eighteen years old; 



 (c) is a permanent resident within the meaning of subsection 2(1) of the Immigration and Refugee Protection Act, has, subject to the regulations, satisfied any condition attached to his or her permanent resident status under that Act and, after becoming a permanent resident: 



 (i) was actually present in Canada for at least one thousand four hundred and sixty days during the six years preceding the date of his application, 



 (ii) was actually present in Canada for at least one hundred and eighty-three days per calendar year during four of the years completely or partially included in the six years preceding the date of his application, 



 (iii) has fulfilled any applicable requirement under the Income Tax Act to submit a return of income for four of the taxation years completely or partially falling within the six years preceding the date of its application; 



